The paper deals with the problem of selecting the largest k elements from a dynamic data model, which involves comparing pairs of elements at each time step. This problem is related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), machine learning (cs.LG), social and information networks (cs.SI), and data mining (cs.DM). Therefore, these are the most likely arXiv CS sub-categories for this paper, ordered from most to least likely.
